The new program is 

benchtwod3mpi_balanced.f

...and is compiled like this (see bench_5_workstations_balanced.sh):

ifort -c /opt/intel/Compiler/11.1/064/mkl/include/mkl_dfti.f90

/opt/openmpi/bin/mpifort -O3 -tpp7 -xW -cm -no-prec-div -w -openmp \
-L/opt/intel/Compiler/11.1/064/mkl/lib/em64t -lmkl_intel_lp64 \
-lmkl_intel_thread -lmkl_core \
-I/opt/intel/composer_xe_2015.0.090/mkl/include \
benchtwod3mpi_balanced.f mkl_dfti.o -o benchtwod3mpi_balanced

...and is run like this (where the -hosts option must be specified
in exactly the order shown -hosts eccles,thynne,mori,core64rr,core48):

/opt/openmpi/bin/mpirun --bind-to none -x LD_LIBRARY_PATH \
-x OMP_NUM_THREADS=64 -host eccles,thynne,mori,core64rr,core48 -n 5 benchtwod3mpi_balanced

This "balanced" version takes 24 seconds to run, which is 63% of the
old "unbalanced" (equally-apportioned accum loops) time of 38 seconds.

Note that the routine tries to get as many threads (cores) on each machine
(up to a maximum of 64), even if adding more threads does not provide
much of a speedup.

